doc_summary_long: A Frenchman who inherited a house from a dead relative has discovered a glittering treasure trove of gold coins and bars worth millions. Squirrelled away in hiding places throughout the house in Normandy, he came across thousands of gold coins and bars weighing 100kg (220lb) in total. Fierfort, who had visited the house to value furniture offered for sale by the new owner, said the loot, which was worth €3.5m ($3.7m), was 'extremely well hidden'.
doc_summary_short: A Frenchman who inherited a house from a dead relative has discovered a glittering treasure trove of gold coins and bars worth millions.
doc_title: French man discovers gold coins and bars worth €3.5m in inherited house
